Package: statesnap
Type: Package
Title: Transport-Agnostic Full-State Capture and Restore
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Iva", family = "Gunjaca", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "gunjaca.iva@gmail.com")
Description: Transport-agnostic full-state serialisation and restoration for
    interactive R applications. Captures a set of inputs and computed values to
    a single JSON string and restores them later, guaranteeing exact
    reproducibility without recomputation. The library produces and consumes
    JSON only; how it is transmitted or persisted (REST, Kafka, Redis, file,
    database) is left to the caller. Typed wrappers handle file references and
    arbitrary binary R objects. Shiny is supported but not required: inputs and
    setters are duck-typed, so the core works with any list-like state and any
    accessor function. Prototype accompanying the ShinySwarm thesis.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    jsonlite,
    base64enc
Suggests:
    shiny,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
